How much compression does your team use to intake cubes and how much for cones? And if your bot doesn’t use the best compression, what do you think the best compression is?

Our claw manipulator can crank down to 1 inch but usually does not go that closed. In prototyping, we found that for a dual roller everybot design with 30A wheels 2-inch wheels 2.75 inch was the best for cones.

That’s too much IMO.

Not sure what the “number” is, but it is plenty. At our 1st regional we were dropping cones, so for our second we replaced (1) 0.5625" piston with (2) 1.125" pistons – now we can crush a whole stack of cones and it’s near impossible for a person to rip a cone out now.

“Overkill is just enough kill”

We didn’t apply a ton of pressure but added suction at the base of our claw while the arm was in motion. Early season prototyping we ran suction alone (no claw) and we were able to place cones and cubes reliably. The challenge was you couldn’t run the vacuum generator continuously so we needed something mechanical to hold the game pieces at least at rest.
